\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\lang9 Text Color\par
The color property is used to set the color of the text. The color is specified by:\par
\par
a color name - like "red"\par
a HEX value - like "#ff0000"\par
an RGB value - like "rgb(255,0,0)"\par
Look at CSS Color Values for a complete list of possible color values.\par
\par
The default text color for a page is defined in the body selector.\par
\par
Example\par
body \{\par
  color: blue;\par
\}\par
\par
h1 \{\par
  color: green;\par
\}\par
\par
\par
--------------------\par
Text Color and Background Color\par
In this example, we define both the background-color property and the color property:\par
\par
Example\par
body \{\par
  background-color: lightgrey;\par
  color: blue;\par
\}\par
\par
h1 \{\par
  background-color: black;\par
  color: white;\par
\}\par
\par
div \{\par
  background-color: blue;\par
  color: white;\par
\}\par
