\b CSS Text Alignment\par
Text Alignment and Text Direction\par
\b0 In this chapter you will learn about the following properties:\par
\b\par
text-align\par
text-align-last\par
direction\par
unicode-bidi\par
vertical-align\par
Text Alignment\par
\b0 The text-align property is used to set the horizontal alignment of a text.\par
\par
A text can be left or right aligned, centered, or justified.\par
\par
The following example shows center aligned, and left and right aligned text (left alignment is default if text direction is left-to-right, and right alignment is default if text direction is right-to-left):\par
\par
Example\par
h1 \{\par
  text-align: center;\par
\}\par
\par
h2 \{\par
  text-align: left;\par
\}\par
\par
h3 \{\par
  text-align: right;\par
\}\par
When the text-align property is set to "justify", each line is stretched so that every line has equal width, and the left and right margins are straight (like in magazines and newspapers):\par
\par
Example\par
div \{\par
  text-align: justify;\par
\}\par
\b Text Align Last\par
\b0 The text-align-last property specifies how to align the last line of a text.\par
\par
Example\par
Align the last line of text in three <p> elements:\par
\par
p.a \{\par
  text-align-last: right;\par
\}\par
\par
p.b \{\par
  text-align-last: center;\par
\}\par
\par
p.c \{\par
  text-align-last: justify;\par
\}\par
Text Direction\par
The direction and unicode-bidi properties can be used to change the text direction of an element:\par
\par
Example\par
p \{\par
  direction: rtl;\par
  unicode-bidi: bidi-override;\par
\}\par
\b Vertical Alignment\par
\b0 The vertical-align property sets the vertical alignment of an element.\par
\par
Example\par
Set the vertical alignment of an image in a text: \par
\par
img.a \{\par
  vertical-align: baseline;\par
\}\par
\par
img.b \{\par
  vertical-align: text-top;\par
\}\par
\par
img.c \{\par
  vertical-align: text-bottom;\par
\}\par
\par
img.d \{\par
  vertical-align: sub;\par
\}\par
\par
img.e \{\par
  vertical-align: super;\par
\}\par
\b The CSS Text Alignment/Direction Properties\par
\b0 Property\tab    Description\par
direction\tab    Specifies the text direction/writing direction\par
text-align\tab    Specifies the horizontal alignment of text\par
text-align-last\tab     Specifies how to align the last line of a text\par
unicode-bidi\tab     Used together with the direction property to set or return whether the text       should be overridden to support multiple languages in the same document                          \par
vertical-align\tab     Sets the vertical alignment of an element\par
