\b CSS Text Decoration\par
Text Decoration\par
\b0 In this chapter you will learn about the following properties:\par
\par
text-decoration-line\par
text-decoration-color\par
text-decoration-style\par
text-decoration-thickness\par
text-decoration\par
Add a Decoration Line to Text\par
The text-decoration-line property is used to add a decoration line to text.\par
\par
Tip: You can combine more than one value, like overline and underline to display lines both over and under a text.\par
\par
Example\par
h1 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: overline;\par
\}\par
\par
h2 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: line-through;\par
\}\par
\par
h3 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
\}\par
\par
p \{\par
  text-decoration-line: overline underline;\par
\}\par
Note: It is not recommended to underline text that is not a link, as this often confuses the reader.\par
\par
Specify a Color for the Decoration Line\par
The text-decoration-color property is used to set the color of the decoration line.\par
\par
Example\par
h1 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: overline;\par
  text-decoration-color: red;\par
\}\par
\par
h2 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: line-through;\par
  text-decoration-color: blue;\par
\}\par
\par
h3 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
  text-decoration-color: green;\par
\}\par
\par
p \{\par
  text-decoration-line: overline underline;\par
  text-decoration-color: purple;\par
\}\par
\par
Specify a Style for the Decoration Line\par
The text-decoration-style property is used to set the style of the decoration line.\par
\par
Example\par
h1 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
  text-decoration-style: solid;\par
\}\par
\par
h2 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
  text-decoration-style: double;\par
\}\par
\par
h3 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
  text-decoration-style: dotted;\par
\}\par
\par
p.ex1 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
  text-decoration-style: dashed;\par
\}\par
\par
p.ex2 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
  text-decoration-style: wavy;\par
\}\par
\par
p.ex3 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
  text-decoration-color: red;\par
  text-decoration-style: wavy;\par
\}\par
Specify the Thickness for the Decoration Line\par
The text-decoration-thickness property is used to set the thickness of the decoration line.\par
\par
Example\par
h1 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
  text-decoration-thickness: auto;\par
\}\par
\par
h2 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
  text-decoration-thickness: 5px;\par
\}\par
\par
h3 \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
  text-decoration-thickness: 25%;\par
\}\par
\par
p \{\par
  text-decoration-line: underline;\par
  text-decoration-color: red;\par
  text-decoration-style: double;\par
  text-decoration-thickness: 5px;\par
\}\par
The Shorthand Property\par
The text-decoration property is a shorthand property for:\par
\par
text-decoration-line (required)\par
text-decoration-color (optional)\par
text-decoration-style (optional)\par
text-decoration-thickness (optional)\par
Example\par
h1 \{\par
  text-decoration: underline;\par
\}\par
\par
h2 \{\par
  text-decoration: underline red;\par
\}\par
\par
h3 \{\par
  text-decoration: underline red double;\par
\}\par
\par
p \{\par
  text-decoration: underline red double 5px;\par
\}\par
A Small Tip\par
All links in HTML are underlined by default. Sometimes you see that links are styled with no underline. The text-decoration: none; is used to remove the underline from links, like this:\par
\par
Example\par
a \{\par
  text-decoration: none;\par
\}\par
All CSS text-decoration Properties\par
Property\tab Description\par
text-decoration\tab Sets all the text-decoration properties in one declaration\par
text-decoration-color\tab Specifies the color of the text-decoration\par
text-decoration-line\tab Specifies the kind of text decoration to be used (underline, overline, etc.)\par
text-decoration-style\tab Specifies the style of the text decoration (solid, dotted, etc.)\par
text-decoration-thickness\tab Specifies the thickness of the text decoration line\par
