\b CSS Text Transformation\par
Text Transformation\par
\b0 The text-transform property is used to specify uppercase and lowercase letters in a text.\par
\par
It can be used to turn everything into uppercase or lowercase letters, or capitalize the first letter of each word:\par
\par
Example\par
p.uppercase \{\par
  text-transform: uppercase;\par
\}\par
\par
p.lowercase \{\par
  text-transform: lowercase;\par
\}\par
\par
p.capitalize \{\par
  text-transform: capitalize;\par
\}\par
The CSS Text Transformation Property\par
Property\tab Description\par
text-transform\tab Controls the capitalization of text\par
