\b CSS Text Spacing\par
Text Spacing\par
\b0 In this chapter you will learn about the following properties:\par
\par
text-indent\par
letter-spacing\par
line-height\par
word-spacing\par
white-space\par
Text Indentation\par
The text-indent property is used to specify the indentation of the first line of a text:\par
\par
Example\par
p \{\par
  text-indent: 50px;\par
\}\par
Letter Spacing\par
The letter-spacing property is used to specify the space between the characters in a text.\par
\par
The following example demonstrates how to increase or decrease the space between characters:\par
\par
Example\par
h1 \{\par
  letter-spacing: 5px;\par
\}\par
\par
h2 \{\par
  letter-spacing: -2px;\par
\}\par
Line Height\par
The line-height property is used to specify the space between lines:\par
\par
Example\par
p.small \{\par
  line-height: 0.8;\par
\}\par
\par
p.big \{\par
  line-height: 1.8;\par
\}\par
\par
Word Spacing\par
The word-spacing property is used to specify the space between the words in a text.\par
\par
The following example demonstrates how to increase or decrease the space between words:\par
\par
Example\par
p.one \{\par
  word-spacing: 10px;\par
\}\par
\par
p.two \{\par
  word-spacing: -2px;\par
\}\par
White Space\par
The white-space property specifies how white-space inside an element is handled.\par
\par
This example demonstrates how to disable text wrapping inside an element:\par
\par
Example\par
p \{\par
  white-space: nowrap;\par
\}\par
The CSS Text Spacing Properties\par
Property\tab Description\par
letter-spacing\tab Specifies the space between characters in a text\par
line-height\tab Specifies the line height\par
text-indent\tab Specifies the indentation of the first line in a text-block\par
white-space\tab Specifies how to handle white-space inside an element\par
word-spacing\tab Specifies the space between words in a text\par
