\b CSS Text Shadow\par
Text Shadow\par
\b0 The text-shadow property adds shadow to text.\par
\par
In its simplest use, you only specify the horizontal shadow (2px) and the vertical shadow (2px):\par
\par
Text shadow effect!\par
Example\par
h1 \{\par
  text-shadow: 2px 2px;\par
\}\par
Next, add a color (red) to the shadow:\par
\par
Text shadow effect!\par
Example\par
h1 \{\par
  text-shadow: 2px 2px red;\par
\}\par
Then, add a blur effect (5px) to the shadow:\par
\par
Text shadow effect!\par
Example\par
h1 \{\par
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 5px red;\par
\}\par
More Text Shadow Examples\par
Example 1\par
Text-shadow on a white text:\par
\par
h1 \{\par
  color: white;\par
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px #000000;\par
\}\par
Example 2\par
Text-shadow with red neon glow:\par
\par
h1 \{\par
  text-shadow: 0 0 3px #ff0000;\par
\}\par
Example 3\par
Text-shadow with red and blue neon glow:\par
\par
h1 \{\par
  text-shadow: 0 0 3px #ff0000, 0 0 5px #0000ff;\par
\}\par
Example 4\par
h1 \{\par
  color: white;\par
  text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px black, 0 0 25px blue, 0 0 5px darkblue;\par
\}\par
