CSS Fonts\par
Choosing the right font for your website is important!\par
\par
Font Selection is Important\par
Choosing the right font has a huge impact on how the readers experience a website.\par
\par
The right font can create a strong identity for your brand.\par
\par
Using a font that is easy to read is important. The font adds value to your text. It is also important to choose the correct color and text size for the font.\par
\par
Generic Font Families\par
In CSS there are five generic font families:\par
\par
Serif fonts have a small stroke at the edges of each letter. They create a sense of formality and elegance.\par
Sans-serif fonts have clean lines (no small strokes attached). They create a modern and minimalistic look.\par
Monospace fonts - here all the letters have the same fixed width. They create a mechanical look. \par
Cursive fonts imitate human handwriting.\par
Fantasy fonts are decorative/playful fonts.\par
All the different font names belong to one of the generic font families. \par
\par
Difference Between Serif and Sans-serif Fonts\par
Serif vs. Sans-serif\par
Note: On computer screens, sans-serif fonts are considered easier to read than serif fonts.\par
\par
Some Font Examples\par
